In the planning part of this meeting, we mapped out the FigJam board from the start with the different deliverables sectioned off  
![][image1]

Sprint planning event:  
1\. The date, time and duration (less than 2 weeks) of the Sprint Planning Event;   
2\. The allocation of roles (Scrum Master, Product Owner, and Developers);   
3\. The expected frequency of Daily Scrums (e.g., 2-3 days per week); and   
4\. The newly created Sprint backlog with refined product backlog items added – usually between 2-5 everyday user stories or perhaps 2-5 “spikes” depending on the Sprint timebox as well as the size and readiness of those stories and the item prioritisation order (as defined by the Proxy Product Owner).

Each Sprint is expected to result in the following documentable Scrum Artifacts:  
1\. An evolving version of the Product Backlog \[2\];   
2\. A Sprint Backlog containing the refined backlog items;   
3\. The Definition of Done for the Sprint;   
4\. A Velocity Chart; and   
5\. The Product Increment itself. 

During each Sprint, the Scrum Master is expected to facilitate each of the following Scrum Events:   
1\. Sprint Planning Event;   
2\. Daily Scrum Events;   
3\. Sprint Review Event;  
4\. Sprint Retrospective Event.
